      "slides": [
        {
          "slideName": "What is a Pitch?",
          "slideType": "Information",
          "slideMedia": [
            {
              "filename": "Intro_SwingAndMiss.mp4",
              "caption": "Make the batter swing and miss:",
              "captionLocation": "top"
            },
            {
              "filename": "Intro_StrikeZone.mp4",
              "caption": "Throw a pitch in the \"strike zone\" (white box):",
              "captionLocation": "top"
            }
          ],
          "slideText": "In baseball, the pitcher’s goal is to get a strike, which leads to an out.\nThere are two ways to get a strike:"
        },
        {
          "slideName": "Pitch Velocity",
          "slideType": "Information",
          "slideMedia": [
            {
              "filename": "Intro_PitchVelocityEdited.mp4",
              "caption": "Nick Pivetta, Boston Red Sox",
              "captionLocation": "bottom"
            }
          ],
          "slideText": "To throw off the batter, pitchers throw different “types” of pitces.\nPitch speed, or velocity, is often the best indicator of what type of pitch is thrown."
        },
        {
          "slideName": "Pitch Movement",
          "slideType": "Information",
          "slideMedia": [
            {
              "filename": "Intro_PitchMovement1.mp4",
              "caption": "The Pitch \"Breaks\":",
              "captionLocation": "top"
            },
            {
              "filename": "Intro_PitchMovement2.mp4",
              "caption": "The Pitch is Straight:",
              "captionLocation": "top"
            }
          ],
          "slideText": "Pitch movement, or the amount it “breaks” down or to the side, is another indicator of what pitch type it is."
        }
      ]
    },
